            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has had 12 min, remove the dish from the oven and top with your <strong>grated cheese</strong> and <strong>chopped pepperoni</strong></p><p>Return the dish to the oven and cook for a further 12-15 min or until the cheese has melted, the pepperoni has crisped and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>cheesy pepperoni chicken</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>salad</strong>, <strong>sliced cucumber</strong> and <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>in a bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>– this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
